# Team workflow

3-person Epitech project, Mac + Windows split, 2 months / Thu+Fri only. The workflow is optimised for minimal friction and zero "it works on my machine".

## Repositories

- **Working repo**: `LenySauzet/Ankhora` (public). All PRs land here.
- **Epitech submission repo**: `EpitechMscProPromo2026/T-VIR-902-MPL_2`. Mirror only â€” never push by hand. CI pushes `main` automatically after each merge.

## Branches

- `main` â€” protected. No direct push. Always shippable.
- Feature branches: `feat/<scope>-<slug>` (e.g. `feat/recorder-hand-capture`).
- Bugfix branches: `fix/<slug>` (e.g. `fix/passthrough-flicker`).
- Chore / infra: `chore/<slug>`.
- Docs only: `docs/<slug>`.

Keep branches short-lived (â‰¤ 2 working days). Rebase often onto `main` before opening a PR.

## Commits â€” Conventional Commits

Every commit must follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```
<type>(<scope>)?: <short imperative summary>

<optional body>

<optional footer>
```

Allowed types: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `perf`, `build`, `ci`, `style`.

Scopes for Ankhora: `recorder`, `playback`, `xr`, `ui`, `domain`, `infra`, `ci`, `docs`, `tooling`.

Example: `feat(recorder): persist hand joints to JSON timeline`.

If you use Claude Code, invoke the `git-commit` skill (`/git-commit`) â€” it generates a conformant message from staged changes.

## Pull Requests

- **One PR per logical change.** No grab-bag PRs.
- Title = a Conventional Commit (since we squash-merge, the PR title becomes the commit message on `main`).
- Description follows `.github/pull_request_template.md`.
- **Required checks before merge**:
  1. GameCI Unity build verify (Quest target) â€” green.
  2. Claude Code review (`anthropics/claude-code-action`) â€” addressed.
  3. CodeRabbit review â€” addressed.
  4. At least one human approval.
- Merge strategy: **squash and merge**. Keeps `main` linear and Conventional-Commits-clean.
- After merge, the mirror workflow auto-pushes `main` to the Epitech repo. Watch the run; if it fails, fix it before walking away.

## Issues & tickets

Tickets live in **GitHub Projects** ("Ankhora" board) attached to `LenySauzet/Ankhora`. Use the issue templates under `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/`. Link issues to PRs via `Closes #NN` in the PR body.

## Code review

- Be specific: cite file:line, propose alternatives, avoid stylistic-only nits already covered by lint or this rule.
- Reply "addressed" with a follow-up commit hash when you act on a comment. Don't resolve a comment unless the requester does or the asker is offline.
- Block on architectural disagreements â€” open an ADR if you can't reach quick consensus.

## ADRs â€” when to write one

Write an ADR under `docs/02-architecture/adr/NNNN-<slug>.md` when you:

- pick a library / SDK over an alternative;
- change Unity Editor version, render pipeline, scripting backend, or target architecture;
- change the data model of a masterclass recording;
- introduce a runtime dependency that touches the build pipeline.

ADR template (use the `mdc` snippet helper):

```markdown
# NNNN â€” <decision title>

- Status: proposed | accepted | superseded by NNNN
- Date: YYYY-MM-DD
- Deciders: <names>

## Context
â€¦

## Decision
â€¦

## Consequences
- Positive: â€¦
- Negative: â€¦
- Neutral: â€¦

## Alternatives considered
â€¦
```
